title: Lutheran withstands battle from Kewaunee
text:
Lutheran withstands battle from Kewaunee Tom Dombeck , HTR Media 10:37 p.m. CDT October 20, 2015 Buy Photo Manitowoc Lutheran's Kelly Herzog (2) and Lindsay Engelbrecht (12) try to block a shot from Kewaunee's Morgan Konop during the first set of Tuesday’s WIAA regional tournament match. (Photo: Yi-Chin Lee/HTR Media) Buy Photo 2 CONNECT 1 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
It wasn’t easy, but the Manitowoc Lutheran volleyball team was able to hold serve and defeat visiting Kewaunee Tuesday in a Division 3 regional opener. 
The No. 2 seeded Lancers swept the No. 7 Storm despite trailing for long stretches in both Games 1 and 3. Lutheran prevailed by scores of 25-23, 25-18, 25-22. 
Anna Menges led the Lancers with six kills and four digs in an all-around effort while Hannah Schleis tallied 12 assists. Also for Lutheran, Maddie Schleis had seven digs while Emily Behnke added seven kills. 
Late in Game 3, the hosts were down 19-13 but closed on a 12-3 run to advance to the regional semifinals. Buy Photo Manitowoc Lutheran volleyball hosts Kewaunee on Tuesday, Oct. 20. Herald Times Reporter: What were you overall thoughts on tonight’s match? 
Anna Menges: Well we started out a little rusty but by the end we picked it up and had a good win. 
HTR: What were the team’s thoughts early on in Game 1 when you were down? 
AM: Basically that we need to start talking and getting quicker on offense. 
HTR: Did you guys think you’d be able to pull it out in Game 1? 
AM: Yeah, we were confident that we were going to win but we had to play hard to do so. 
HTR: What happened in Game 2, you and your teammates really came out firing? 
AM: We were really just kind of mad about the first game, we really wanted to take control of it from the start. 
HTR: What happened in Game 3 when you fell behind pretty early? 
AM: I think we stopped talking and when we get down it’s hard for us to come back but I’m glad that we did. 
HTR: What did coach say in that last timeout when you were down 11-8. 
AM: She said to get quicker on offense because they were blocking us a lot so we had to have decoys and move the ball more. 
HTR: What allowed you to come back in that last game? 
AM: Pretty much playing as a team and having confidence that we could do it. 
HTR: What do you think Lutheran’s chances are in the postseason? 
AM: I think if we play our best we can do pretty well. 
HTR: Do you think a match like tonight where you showed great perseverance will help you later in the postseason? 
AM: Yeah because we’ll probably have those games where we’ll get behind but we need to bounce back so this will definitely help. 2 CONNECT 1 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE Read or Share this story: http://htrne.ws/1RUZDAy TOP VIDEOS
